Sally Lutkin wanted a rose and her grandchildren's names tattooed on her leg . 
  She had a rose surrounded by the names Harvey, seven, Harvey Junior, six and Cooper, one . 
  But the tattoo became infected and became so swollen she was in agony and couldn't walk . 
  She was rushed to hospital for emergency surgery and was in hospital for a week . 
  After the operation she was left with a bloody hole in her leg and a scar in the middle of her calf . 
  She has vowed never to have another tattoo in her life . 
 